Description: Fragment of sub-round handle to sharp turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine light brown.
Curator's comments: Name Polykrates. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 28a, 13. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0198.42.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0654)
